cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.CY, cs.CR, cs.DB

The paper discusses the use of domain taxonomy as a tool for assessing the scope and quality of research, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. cs.DL (Digital Libraries) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are likely categories as they deal with organizing and analyzing large amounts of data, which is similar to the use of taxonomies in this paper. cs.CY (Cryptography and Security) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) are also possible categories as they involve evaluating the quality and impact of research in a specific domain. Finally, cs.DB (Databases) is a possible category as the paper discusses the use of taxonomies to analyze research projects or papers, which is similar to the use of databases to organize and analyze information.
